      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Version-controlled solver with documented test suite; configuration management records available for regulatory review.",
      "rationale": "OpenFOAM v9 deployed under institutional version control (Git). Automated regression test suite (47 cases) executed prior to production runs. Build configuration and solver settings archived in study repository with SHA-256 checksums."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver verified against at least one analytical or manufactured solution benchmark at second-order convergence or better.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to rotating-frame incompressible Navier-Stokes equations. L2 norm error convergence rate 1.98 ± 0.04 across four refinement levels, confirming second-order spatial accuracy. FDA benchmark case CFD-2017-01 reproduced within published tolerances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI < 5% for primary QoI (wall shear stress, hemolysis index) on production mesh.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation-based GCI computed on three-mesh sequence. GCI for volume-averaged hemolysis index: 1.7% (fine-to-medium), 4.3% (medium-to-coarse). Production mesh (5.8M cells) selected as mesh-independent for MRL 2 requirements. y+ < 5 maintained on all blood-contacting surfaces."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions documented and traceable; fluid properties and boundary conditions match computational setup within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro hemolysis experiments conducted using modified index of hemolysis (MIH) protocol per ASTM F1841. Blood analog fluid (bovine whole blood, hematocrit 33±2%) properties measured at 37°C. Flow rates controlled to ±0.05 L/min; pump speed to ±10 RPM. Boundary conditions applied in CFD match experimental measurements within combined uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted RH index within ±20% of experimental values at all 5 operating points; systematic bias < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed at all 5 operating points. Maximum point-wise error: 11.8% at Q=2 L/min, N=3500 RPM. Mean absolute error: 7.3%. No systematic over- or under-prediction bias detected (mean signed error: +1.2%). Validation metric satisfies acceptance criterion at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation directly correspond to decision-relevant outputs (RH index, worst-case operating point identification).",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary regulatory decision metric for 510(k) comparison. Volume-averaged hemolysis index and peak shear stress exposure time are intermediate QoIs directly informing RH calculation. All validation QoIs are mechanistically linked to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted at conditions spanning the CPB operating envelope; geometry matches production device within manufacturing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments span the full 5-point operating envelope (Q: 2–6 L/min, N: 2000–3500 RPM). FDA generic pump geometry used in both CFD and experiments. Impeller clearance gaps replicate nominal manufacturing tolerance (0.3 mm ± 0.05 mm). Fluid temperature, viscosity, and hematocrit representative of intraoperative CPB conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
